narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Good intro to music! If you've done some theory before, though, consider 205--this one starts at the very basics of reading music, then progresses to scales, chords, harmonic analysis, etc. Very chill if you have music experience.

I would definitely recommend this class to another student. Music 110 was a super fun and rewarding course! It can be tedious at times and it is annoying when people who are overqualified (and know it/brag about it when you're alone) stay in it, but your professor understands that if you let him/her know! Take it if you want to get into songwriting or learn some things about whatever instrument you play.
I would recommend the course for musicians only. If you do not play an instrument, the class has little to no relevance for you.

I would recommend this class if you have a musical background but no knowledge of music theory. The first few weeks are spent on learning to read music, which is a bit boring if you can already read it (I could), but after that the class becomes more engaging.

It's a pretty fast moving class, and a little more work than I expected for a 110 class, but the teacher was very nice and gave us both a take-home open note midterm and final. I'd recommend if you want to learn the basics of music theory and chord analysis.
